Tests for input variation behaviors:
Using some 'known' scripts, to test the 'usage' and 'options' functions.
  (interpret '<good>' to mean good input should be provided  )

levels	(No options) 	usage, for missing host
levels	 -h <good> 	correct operation
levels	 -?			usage only, no specific complaint
trim_indices -h <good> -a -c    usage for missing -k option (a,c not known, ignored)
trim_indices -h <good> -ac      usage for missing -k option (a,c not known, ignored)


